📷 @saulriosfotografia

It’s the season to make room for things that fulfill you and your life 🎁🌟
 
Let’s create space for our well-being, our mental health, our inner peace and our health. One of my major lessons in 2022 was to NOT overload my schedule with commitments, family, work, friends and stress. Sometimes we tied productivity with our value as a person and we shouldn’t because we are so much more than the position we hold or the title we hold. Let’s set our goals for 2023 and reach every single one of them❄️ 
 
I encourage you to subtract all the negative and make room for the positive whether that be people that didn’t see your value, whether you are going trough something physically, whether you are going trough something emotionally or even spiritually.
 
📷: @saulriosfotografia

Agradecemos la confianza de @luisalejandrobeauty  por compartir esto con nosotras y por alzar su voz y promover el cuidado de la salud mental🧠 te admiramos y apreciamos el gran impacto que tienes para la comunidad del Valle de Texas!

Si tu o alguien conocido esta sufriendo depresión, ansiedad, ataques de pánico, etc… aquí dejamos varios recursos para ustedes :
•NAMI’s HelpLine at 800-950-NAMI (800-950-6264) or text “NAMI” to 62640. 
•988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline (formerly known as the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline): 988 for English or Spanish, or Lifeline Chat. ...
•Crisis Text Line: Text SIGNS to 741741 for 24/7, anonymous, free crisis counseling.
•Disaster Distress Helpline: CALL or TEXT 1-800-985-5990 (press 2 for Spanish)
